text.tspan: Exports between rich and non-rich countries
The 'rich to non-rich' trade series shows the proportion of global merchandise exports that correspond to sales from
rich countries to non-rich countries. The other series show similar flows within and across these countries. In the
sources you find the complete list of 'rich' and 'non-rich' countries.
Source: CEPII (2016) Two Centuries of Bilateral Trade and Gravity Data: 1827-2014 (2016)
